caption.text:
My parenting skills today are questionable. Bens gone to climb a mountain, we’re staying at my parents for the weekend. Managed to go and watch Sebastian play football this morning. Another win and another goal for him. But since then I am back on the sofa with my foot up while Sebastian plays on his Nintendo. Feeling fed up and my foot feels uncomfortable today, I just want the bandages off and to get some air. On top of that I burnt the roof of my mouth the other day and it’s really sore today and just making me feel crappy. Is it bedtime yet?!?
.
.
.

This brings me back. 
I remember sitting in front of a little TV that we had to get an adapter to plug in our first @nintendo entertainment system. My brother and I (and sometimes our mom) would play the OG Super Mario Brothers and Duck Hunt. We got Castlevania and the Legend of Zelda next. 
Now I see this super portable @nintendoswitches and I can play Zelda and Mario on the go. The controls are a bit small for me in two player mode so I picked up these @mumba.official grips and of course a carrying case to keep it all together. 
Pretty crazy to think I’m 40 now and Super Mario Brothers, Legend Of Zelda and Nintendo (one of the best brand ID’s ever) has been part of my life for over 30 years.

caption.text:
ICYMI - The allegation comes from reliable journalist Zenj Nishikawa, who was reportedly told at developer conference CEDEC that "𝐒𝐨𝐧𝐲 𝐞𝐱𝐞𝐜𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐥𝐚𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐰𝐨 𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐲𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐦𝐨𝐝𝐞𝐥𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐝𝐢𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐢𝐫 𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞.” at the same time.⁣⁣
⁣
The two consoles will be different in performance: one will be a base model (PlayStation 5) and the other a high-end variant (PlayStation 5 Pro) for those after the absolute best gaming experience.⁣⁣
⁣
Xbox was said to be doing something similar until June, when it scrapped Xbox Lockhart (the alleged cheaper variant of Xbox Scarlett) due to development issues and so they could concentrate on their flagship console.⁣⁣
⁣
For now though, take this report with a pinch of salt. We could get some news regarding the next generation of PlayStation this year but it’s becoming increasingly likely it will be unveiled at a dedicated PlayStation Meeting 2020 event on February 21, 2020 (according to a recent leak).⁣⁣
⁣

APPLE ARCADE: TUDO O QUE VOCÊ PRECISA SABER

Preço, compatibilidade e informações do serviço de assinatura de games
Em março de 2019, a Apple anunciou sua mais nova empreitada no mundo dos games: o Apple Arcade.
Disponível tanto para as plataformas mobile quanto computadores e Apple TV, o serviço promete trazer um catálogo de jogos especiais para o público assinante.

Confira abaixo o que é preciso saber sobre o Apple Arcade:

O que é o Apple Arcade?
O Apple Arcade é um serviço de assinatura de games, oferecendo acesso ilimitado a mais de 100 títulos para os dispositivos da Apple, tanto mobile quanto no computador e Apple TV.

Lançamento?
O serviço foi lançado oficialmente para iPhone em 19 de setembro, junto com o iOS 13. A previsão é de que ele chegue em 30 de setembro para iPad e Apple TV, e outubro para MacBook e iMac, junto do sistema operacional macOS Catalina.

Preço?
O Apple Arcade traz um serviço de assinatura de R$ 9,90 por mês, com direito a um mês de teste gratuito.

Jogos?
No lançamento, o Apple Arcade conta com um catálogo de mais de 100 jogos. Entre os títulos de destaque estão Oceanhorn 2, Sayonara Wild Hearts, Hot Lava, Where Cards Fall, Frogger in Toy Town e Shinsekai Into the Depths.

Dispositivos compatíveis?
Para rodar o Apple Arcade, é necessário ter o iOS 13 no iPhone, iPadOS 13 para iPad, tvOS 13 para Apple TV e macOS Catalina para computadores Mac.

Great beer to drink on a cold night, but we have to be careful since the alcohol rate on this one is 13%. And the game is 88 Heroes for the Nintendo Switch. This game is very fun to play, and has hilarious characters. Like the name suggests it has 88 heroes to play with and has to beat 88 levels in 88 seconds each. Swipe left to see the trailer.
Have a great weekend everyone. 
Cheers 🍺🍻.
.
.
.

CONDIVIDI NELLE STORIE ⬇️ Annunciata nell’Agosto del 2005 e completata il mese dopo, l’acquisizione di Taito da parte di Square Enix è un altro dei tanti passi importanti per l’attuale conformazione del settore videoludico. È bene essere a conoscenza delle dinamiche che operano al di sotto del mondo delle meraviglie percepito dagli utenti finali. Dopo la liquidazione di due sussidiarie Taito nel 2008, nonché la creazione di Taito Soft Corporation nel 2010 (a tutti gli effetti in Square Enix), la compagnia ha annunciato la ripresa dell’attività di pubblicazione nel 2018. Con l’avvento della nuova generazione, non è chiaro quali saranno le mosse di Taito e di quale libertà effettiva disponga all’interno del gruppo Square Enix. Il futuro della casa di Space Invaders nel gaming casalingo è avvolto da una nube, ma i suoi affari nel settore arcade vanno molto bene - specificamente in Giappone, dove sono presenti numerose “Taito Station”. Commenta con la tua opinione, tagga un amico e condividi. Inoltre, unisciti al gruppo Telegram di Gamerversum. caption.text:
.
.
Nintendo Switch Lite
.
Yes people! I liked the Normal Nintendo Switch, but that dosen't mean there was  no problems about it... yes the Lite really feels like a Handheld now more than the normal one, The D-Pad, the size, no joycon 👍🏻 and ofcourse the Weight
.
in the end you know what you need better, The Lite or The Old
.
.
جهاز نينتندو سويتش لايت
.
اعجبني سابقاً جهاز نينتندو شويتش، لكن هذا لا يعني ان الجهاز خالي من العيوب... مع جهاز اللايت احسست فعلاً بإمتلاكي لجهاز محمول، زر الإتجاهات او ما يسمى بالدي باد، حجم الجهاز، عدم وجود جوي كونز، و اخيراً الوزن الخفيف
.
في النهاية لا يعني ان الجهاز السابق سيء، لكن به ايجابيات وسلبيات كما هو الحال بالجديد
.
.
.
.

The most played first person game with types of guns and attractvie gameplay.
Developer : @gameloft 
Publisher : gameloft, gameloft se
Downloads : 5 million+
Reviews : 4.2/5

Pros:
- Free to play.
- Fun way to kill time.
- Easy to learn agent's abilities.
- Partner up with squads.
- Half of the agents are easy to unlock.

Cons:
- Unbalanced matchmaking system.
- Kult and Blaze are far too OP.
- No team chat communication.
- No friendslist in game.
- Lacking more modes.
- Somewhat difficult to report suspicious gameplay.
- Pay to win (Thats to be expected). #infoshop786
